cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper investigates the latency performance comparison of NOMA and OMA in finite blocklength regime, which is a topic related to information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper studies the link layer rate performance of NOMA and OMA in a two-users network, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers delay quality-of-service constraints in the network, which is a topic related to systems and control.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance comparison of NOMA and OMA in terms of link-layer rate, which is a topic related to multimedia applications.
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses simulations to show the performance of NOMA and OMA, which is a topic related to computational engineering.
